  <h1>
   display_get_gui_width
  </h1>
  With this function you can get the height (in pixels) of the GUI as used in the
  <a href="../../../The_Asset_Editors/Object_Properties/Draw_Events.htm">
   Draw GUI Event
  </a>
  .
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">display_get_gui_height();
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">ads_move(0, display_get_gui_height() - ads_get_display_height(0), 0);
</code></pre>
  The above code will set an advert to display at the bottom left-hand corner of the display.
 </body>
